header.gameNote: LITTLE CAESARS HORIZON LEAGUE MEN'S CHAMPIONSHIP - SEMIFINAL

article.description: Mark Alstork scored 18, and JT Yoho added 15 points -- including the go-ahead jumper with 24 seconds to play -- to lead third-seeded Wright State past No. 2 seed Oakland 59-55 Monday night in the
article.headline: Wright State beats Oakland 59-55 in Horizon League semis
article.linkText: Wright State beats Oakland 59-55 in Horizon League semis
article.story: DETROIT -- Mark Alstork scored 18, and JT Yoho added 15 points -- including the go-ahead jumper with 24 seconds to play -- to lead third-seeded Wright State past No. 2 seed Oakland 59-55 Monday night in the semifinals of the Horizon League tournament. Daniel Mortensen hit three 3s and finished with 11 for the Raiders (22-12), who will face fourth-seeded Green Bay (21-12) in the championship game Tuesday night. Jalen Hayes converted a 3-point play to put Oakland (21-11) up 52-50 with three minutes left. Mortensen answered with a 3-pointer and, after Kay Felder hit two free throws for the Golden Grizzlies, a jumper by Biggie Minnis gave Wright State a one-point lead with 58 seconds remaining. Felder hit 1 of 2 free throws to tie it at 55-all seven seconds later, but Minnis found Yoho for a jumper and then Felder missed a driving layup. Alstork made two foul shots with 10 seconds left to seal it. Felder led Oakland with 18 points on 5-of-19 shooting. Hayes scored 14 with 10 rebounds. Oakland's Max Hooper hit three 3-pointers and finished with nine points. His father, Chip Hooper, died last Saturday after a four-year battle with cancer.
